comment:
As much as I appreciate that YouTube content creators need stuff to make videos on and opinion based content will be made, I believe the reason that YouTube demonetise videos with content mentioning a libel trial - should it not come from a reputable news company such as Sky News and CNN etc; is because there is a risk of being sued for libel under the Defamation Act 2013. 

Any statement which could pose a risk of serious harm to his/hers reputation can be brought to trial under the 2013 act. There are defences of course, and honest opinion is one of them but you have to prove that the statements are of honest opinion, and if the case is brought in London, the writer/speaker has to prove that whichever defence path you have chosen to go down that you had every right to say that. 

Before I get hate on this, I just want to point out that I am just trying to say why I believe that YouTube demonetises videos with potentially libellous statements in them, also until the judge rules his findings in the case it is still up in the air of whether or not whichever side has the truth element added onto it. So the other reason could be that YouTube is showing that your video might not be the truth and that is why it hasn't gained money or isn't getting shown in the first few videos upon which you search for.
